More than 400,000 people face starvation in Turkana, West Pokot and parts of Baringo due to drought. At least 50,000 children have dropped out of school.MPs from the region have urged the government to declare drought in North Rift a national disaster and save humans and livestock. Most of the affected are nomadic communities. More than 200,000 have crossed the border into Uganda in search of pasture and water.&ldquo;The situation is critical and we urge both the national and county governments to move with speed because many people will lose their lives,&rdquo; Baringo North MP William Cheptumo said.Other MPs urging government intervention are Baringo woman representative Grace Kiptui, Asman Kamama (Tiaty), Christopher Nakuleu (Turkana North), Samuel Moroto (Kapenguria) and Protus Akuja (Loima).